PrecisAuthority to enter into a Settlement Agreement (the KAWACATOOSE BAND TREATY LAND ENTITLEMENT SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT) between the Crown, the Kawacatoose Band of Indians and the Province of Saskatchewan, for the purpose of resolving a specific claim associated with the setting apart of reserve land as provided for in Treaty No. 4 of September 15, 1874.

Authority to enter into a Settlement Agreement (the KAWACATOOSE BAND TREATY
LAND ENTITLEMENT SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT) between the Crown, the Kawacatoose
Band of Indians and the Province of Saskatchewan, for the purpose of
resolving a specific claim associated with the setting apart of reserve
land as provided for in Treaty No. 4 of September 15, 1874.
